      <section eId="sec_49_3_6">
        <num>49-3-6</num>
        <content>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1937, p. 355, § 13; Ga. L. 1995, p. 1302, § 14; Ga. L. 1997, p. 1021, § 7; Ga. L. 2009, p. 453, §§ 2-2, 2-3/HB 228; Ga. L. 2015, p. 422, § 5-100/HB 310; Ga. L. 2015, p. 552, § 3/SB 138; Ga. L. 2017, p. 585, § 1-5/SB 174.)</p>
          <p>The 2015 amendments.
      The first 2015 amendment, effective July 1, 2015, inserted "juvenile" preceding "probation officer" in the last sentence of the previously existing provisions of this Code section. The second 2015 amendment, effective July 1, 2015, rewrote this Code section. See Code Commission note regarding the effect of these amendments.</p>
          <p>The 2017 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2017, in subsection (a), substituted "or" for "and" in paragraph (a)(1), deleted "and" at the end of paragraph (a)(3), added paragraph (a)(4), and redesignated former paragraph (a)(4) as present paragraph (a)(5).</p>
        </content>
      </section>
